  "prompt": "What are the differences and similarities between Gary Johnson and Bernie Sanders?",
  "response": "Here are some key differences and similarities between Gary Johnson and Bernie Sanders:\n\nDifferences:\n1. Political Party\n- Gary Johnson: Libertarian\n- Bernie Sanders: Democrat (self-described democratic socialist)\n\n2. Economic Policy\n- Johnson: Supports free market, minimal government intervention\n- Sanders: Supports significant government involvement, stronger social programs\n\n3. Role of Government\n- Johnson: Advocates for smaller government\n- Sanders: Supports expanded government role in healthcare, education, etc.\n\n4. Taxation\n- Johnson: Supports lower taxes, simpler tax code\n- Sanders: Advocates for higher taxes on wealthy, more progressive taxation\n\nSimilarities:\n1. Social Issues\n- Both support personal freedoms\n- Both oppose government restrictions on personal choices\n- Both support marijuana legalization\n\n2. Foreign Policy\n- Both were critical of extensive military interventions\n- Both opposed Iraq War\n- Both skeptical of excessive military spending\n\n3. Political Outsider Status\n- Both seen as non-traditional candidates challenging established political systems\n- Both attracted support from voters dissatisfied with mainstream politics\n\n4. Civil Liberties\n- Both support individual rights\n- Both opposed government surveillance programs\n\nThese comparisons reflect their positions during the 2016 presidential election cycle.",
